# Netscape HTTP Cookie File template
#
# This file is OPTIONAL. yt-dlp can use it to authenticate when downloading
# age-restricted, private, or member-only videos. Without it the app will
# still work for public videos.
#
# To populate it:
#   1. Install a browser extension that exports cookies in "Netscape" format,
#      e.g. "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" (Chrome) or "cookies.txt" (Firefox).
#   2. Log into YouTube in that browser.
#   3. Export cookies for youtube.com and save them as `cookies.txt` (no .example).
#   4. Either drop the file in this project root, OR point the app at it via
#      the "Cookies file" field at the top of the window.
#
# This template file is checked in so it shows up in the repo. The real
# cookies.txt is gitignored so you never accidentally commit credentials.
#
# Format example (one cookie per line, TAB-separated):
# .youtube.com   TRUE   /   TRUE   1735689600   CONSENT   YES+cb
